// classes.nc — Classes in NATCOM
// Demonstrates object-oriented programming in plain English.

// ─── Define a Car class ────────────────────────────────────────────────
Define a class named Car:
  Create a floating point variable named Speed and set it to 0.
  Create a floating point variable named Fuel and set it to 100.
End class.

// ─── Define a Person class ─────────────────────────────────────────────
Define a class named Person:
  Create a high speed integer named Age and set it to 0.
End class.

// ─── Main program ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Display "=== NATCOM Classes Demo ===".
Print a blank line.

// Create objects from the classes
Create an object of class Car named MyCar.
Create an object of class Person named Beon.

Display "Objects created successfully!".
Display "A Car object named MyCar is ready.".
Display "A Person object named Beon is ready.".

Print a blank line.
Display "Classes allow you to group related data together.".
Display "NATCOM OOP: as easy as writing a sentence.".
